Fabric construction is a systematic whole, which focuses on the structure of the fabric. How are fabrics produced, how to mark and derive different applications, how to put theoretical knowledge into practice - these are the main issues to be discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The fabric construction course - the theoretical foundations for weaving - introduces the main principles of loom weaving and gives an overview of the options of loom weaving of different fabrics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows the construction of looms and can set up the warp to the looms. The student knows the basic structures of fabric and can set them to the looms.
